review_blob: Vinmonopolet, Norway. Pours copper yellow. Nose is citrusy, fruity. Light to medium body. Taste is all about the hops (as expected). Big citrus IPA (pine and grape). Bitterness is quite strong, but balances the beer perfectly.

Bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours dark red/brownish. Thin off-white head. Caramel, dried fruits and som smokeiness. Medium body. Nice malty taste; sweet caramel, hint of the peated malt and a light finishing bitterness. Enjoyable.
Vinmonopolet, Kr.sund. Pours light copper yellow. Spicy on the nose. Medium body. Fruity taste, some banana, spices and yeast. Enjoyable tripel.

Bottle from Mother Kellys, London. Pours black with thin head. Oak and coffee on the nose. Medium to full body. Taste is roasted barley, coffee, chocolate and a good dose of sweetness. Sweetness is well balanced out by the bitterness. Top beer!
Bottle from Mother Kelly, London. Pours light copper yellow. Fruity nose, dominated by grape and pine. Medium body. Big hoppy taste and a beautiful punchy bitterness. Truly a must drink beer.

Bottle from Vinmonopolet, Kristiansund. Pours black with brown head. Nose is burnt malts and coffee. Quite light bodied for an imperial stout. Taste is burnt coffee and a tiny smokey aftertaste. An easy drinking imperial stout. All over a good beer from a high quality micro brewery.

Bottle from Beermoth, Manchester. Pours black as the night. Brown caramel head. Heavy body. Sweet aroma. Sweet taste from the bourbon aging, together with rosted barley, coffee, chocolate. Really enjoyable beer from De Molen.

Bottle from Beermoth, Manchester. Pours black with brown head. Strong coffee and chocolate aroma. Medium to heavy body. Taste is big. Roasted malts, coffee, chocolate, dark fruits. Nice roasty bitterness. 11.8 abv well hidden. Thumbs up, Buxton!

Bottle. Pours copper coloured, with light head. Hoppy, floral, caramel, citrus. Boozy. Everything youd wish for. Bitter finish with the hops lasting long. Medium to heavy body. Massive beer. An absolute must try. And try. And try...
Flaske. Lyst gult l, med kritthvitt bra skum. Godt sitruspreg og lav bitterhet. Tynn og lett kropp. Alt i alt et fint l. Vil nok fungere utmerket en varm sommerdag.
Bottle from BeerCentral, Sheffield. Red amber coloured. Hazy, off-white head. Quite malty with distinctly caramel. Light hops. Medium body. Aftertast is bitterness dominated. Enjoyable beer.
